Bliss for GCC
*************

This is a BLISS compiler for linux. It is currently the official 'GNU
BLISS' and it is intended to integrate it with the GCC compiler at a
later stage.

It is at an early stage of development and is made available for
information only - it would not be any use to anyone at this stage.

It is probably fairly portable to other Unix-like operating systems as
well. For DOS and its successors there will be some issues (file name
delimiters, line delimiters, command line length, BSOD) but it is
probably do-able.

See progress to date below for the functions delivered.

See bliss.texi, tree.texi or the html files generated from them for a
list of files and their functions and all the other documentation.

